-- Sri Lanka Leads South Africa by 426 Runs After Day Three of Second Test
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2011-12-28T15:43:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/sri-lanka-leads-south-africa-by-426-runs-after-day-three-of-second-test.html
Sri Lanka  was 256-7 in its second
innings when bad light ended play on day three of the second
cricket Test against South Africa in Durban, a lead of 426 runs
over the hosts.  Kumar Sangakkara hit 108, while wicketkeeper Dinesh
Chandimal, on Test debut, scored 54 -- his second half-century
of the match. Thisara Perera is 6 not out, with Rangana Herath
unbeaten on 5.  Dale Steyn  was South Africa’s leading bowler with
3-54.  Yesterday, South Africa was bowled out for 168 in response
to Sri Lanka’s first innings 338.  South Africa won the opening game of the three-Test series
in Centurion by an innings and 81 runs.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
